snippet.textDisplay:
Abe Lincoln along with George Washington are still some of the greatest presidents in US history. The civil war was a huge mess. Besides the fighting for slavery stuff I still remember learning there some people in the war who merely fought for there home state’s side rather than for the country in of itself. Like Robert E Lee who actually was a decent guy who actually didn’t like slavery all too much.
I actually like the dude even if he did side with the confederates. I am still upset about the fact a statue of him was taken down near where I live. I know he was on the side for slavery but the guy wasn’t an evil man as far as I was concerned. It’s a bit sad really. Hell every part of the civil war is sad.
